CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 20, 1941, pg. 9, reads: "Newlyweds of the Week - Among one of the season's loveliest brides was Miss Ella Mae Fullam, who was married to Thurston Mosely. The ceremony was performed Monday, Sept. 15 at the Monumental Baptist church. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of wedding party with eight men, including groom Thurston Mosely; six women, including bride Ella Mae Fullam Mosely, and flower girl, standing in interior with checkered floor
